Similarly to p-n junction PV devices, the power of a SC device can be related to its electric field-current (E-J) curve. As shown in Fig. 1b, this curve connects open and short circuit scenarios corresponding to infinite and vanishing external resistance, respectively. Additionally, the short circuit current Jshort is equal to the shift current JSC. The maximum generated power is then the rectangle with the largest area drawn underneath the curve connecting open and short circuit end points. By introducing an E-J fill factor F, we get1PPV=FJshort⋅Eopen.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
